headline: How Recent Developments Are Rewriting the Story for National Bank of Greece
summary: The consensus analyst price target for National Bank of Greece has increased from €13.67 to €13.93, marking a modest upgrade in anticipated fair value for the bank’s shares. This slight rise is supported by improved revenue growth expectations and renewed optimism in the bank’s underlying business momentum. headline: How Recent Developments Are Rewriting the Story for JPMorgan Chase

This rise follows a period of more positive analyst sentiment, fueled by recent earnings beats and upward adjustments to the bank’s financial guidance.
